<TITLE> Envoy to UAE gets term extension </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.co)The government has extended the contractual appointment of ATM Nazimullah Chowdhury as Bangladesh ambassador to the United Arab Emirates, who faces corruption charges. The appointment has been extended from May 21 to June 30, the government said in a circular Wednesday. The Anticorruption Commission had filed a corruption case against him for misusing government funds, which cost the state coffers Tk 21 lakh in losses, according to case details. Nazmul Quaunine will replace Nazimullah as Bangladesh ambassador to the UAE after the end of his term in June. Quaunine has been serving as a director general in charge of the Europe Desk at the foreign ministry. bdn
